The '''Indian Chemical Society''' is a [[scientific society]] dedicated in the field of [[chemistry]] from [[India]].<ref>{{cite journal|title=The Indian Chemical Society (1924â€“1932)|journal=Nature|date=1934|volume=133|issue=3369|page=791|doi=10.1038/133791b0}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Indian Chemical Society|url=http://www.indianchemicalsociety.com/|work=indianchemicalsociety.com|accessdate=3 May 2014}}</ref>  It was established in 1924 with [[Prafulla Chandra Ray]] as its founding president.<ref name=jcs1>{{cite book|last=Uma Dasgupta|title=Science and Modern India: An Institutional History, C. 1784-1947|date=2011|publisher=Pearson Education India|page=833|url=https://books.google.com/?id=lrx3wLz4itkC&pg=PA833&dq=indian+chemical+society#v=onepage&q=indian%20chemical%20society&f=false|isbn=9788131728185}}</ref> The same year the society started to publish its "Quarterly Journal of Indian Chemical Society" (1924- 1927) which is currently known as '''Journal of Indian Chemical Society'''.<ref>{{cite book|last=Caroline Cooper|title=Organic Chemist's Desk Reference|date=2010|publisher=CRC Press|isbn=978-1439811641|page=19|url=https://books.google.com/?id=OQrIk2rlduAC&pg=PA19&lpg=PA19&dq=journal+nature+1924+journal+of+indian+chemical+society#v=onepage&q=journal%20nature%201924%20journal%20of%20indian%20chemical%20society&f=false}}</ref><ref name="jcs1"/>

